title: Knees are being destroyed by SL 5x5 via /r/Fitness
body:
Hi,

I started SL 5x5 around 9 weeks ago and I started light on squats at 40kg and now I’m up to 110kg. The last 2 weeks my knees have just been incredibly godamn sore because of the heavy squats 3 times a week. I’m able to complete my sets fully and I start to struggle usually on the last 2 sets but I still manage to get the reps out.

But yeah, my knees are just really hurting, my left knee especially just feels really bruised right now and I’m worried if I keep going I’ll fuck it up.

Has anybody experienced this? What do you guys suggest to do? Shall I take a week out from squatting and just keep doing the other two lifts that follow squats?

Thanks.

via reddit https://ift.tt/2yUkYIR

Pure cardio on a Tuesday morning emotions in order: 😴😭💪(and still 😴)

Feeling good and proud that we woke up early again! I am determined to stay motivated throughout the rest of this program and meet my goals.

Also, Robbie is pleased with our morning work outs because it means he gets to hang out with us an hour longer in the morning! He’s a cutie ❤
